headlines.description: — Even though the Los Angeles Clippers were missing Paul George, there weren't any doubts on who they were going to with the game on the line Saturday against the Orlando Magic.
headlines.shortLinkText: Reggie Jackson hits winning jumper, Clippers beat Magic

headlines.description: — Donovan Mitchell scored 28 points, Rudy Gobert had 20 points and 11 rebounds and the Utah Jazz extended their winning streak to seven games with a 123-98 victory over the Washington Wizards on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jazz beat Wizards 123-98, extend winning streak to 7 games

headlines.description: — Rookie Evan Mobley had 15 points and a season-high 15 rebounds and the Cleveland Cavaliers matched their team record with 81 first-half points in a 117-103 victory over the Sacramento Kings on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Cavaliers score 81 points in first half, beat Kings 117-103

headlines.description: — Duncan Robinson scored a season high-26 points and the Miami Heat beat the short-handed Chicago Bulls 118-92 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Robinson scores season-high 26 points, Heat beat Bulls

headlines.description: — Dillon Brooks scored 25 points, Desmond Bane added 19 points and the Memphis Grizzlies held on for a 113-106 victory over the Houston Rockets on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Brooks, Bane lead Grizzlies past Rockets 113-106

headlines.description: — Stephen Curry had one 3-point shot swatted away out of nowhere by Matisse Thybulle and the Philadelphia defender got him again on a block that sent the ball flying.
headlines.shortLinkText: 76ers delay Curry's 3-point record bid, beat Warriors 102-93

events.name: Denver Nuggets at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — The Denver Nuggets responded to their worst loss of the season just as coach Michael Malone had hoped.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jokic, Nuggets avenge loss to Spurs with 127-112 victory
